For African hair, this has to be the most stressful time, especially if you do not know how to do it yourself. Lockdown means no salons and definitely no house calls, but you can learn something new. During this time a long lasting hairstyle, which is also easy to do, is the way to go to avoid wearing a head wrap every day. Here are five hairstyle that might help you get through this lockdown looking sane: 1. Benny and Betty  2. Bantu Knots  3. Cornrows  4. Go brush short  5. The Kendrick hair Cut  